# 1) Force HTTP → HTTPS (keeps the same host)
http://*   https://:splat   301!

# 2) Canonicalize www → apex (PRIMARY = reedssolutionsllc.org)
https://www.reedssolutionsllc.org/*   https://reedssolutionsllc.org/:splat   301!

# (Optional) If the *other* domain variant exists in DNS, also collapse its www:
https://www.reedsolutionsllc.org/*    https://reedsolutionsllc.org/:splat    301!

# 3) Proper 404 handling for missing routes (DO NOT use SPA fallback for a multi-page site)
#    This SERVES 404.html without redirecting back to /, which avoids loops.
 /*   /404.html   404
